cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.GR, cs.NA. 

The paper deals with Voronoi diagrams and Delaunay triangulations, which are fundamental computational geometry structures, and analyzes their behavior under continuous motion of the input points. This makes cs.CG (Computational Geometry) the most likely category. The paper also mentions the Davenport-Schinzel sequence, which is a well-known topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of the kinetic data structure (KDS) framework suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as another possible category. The paper also discusses the topological changes in the structures, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
